Runtime composition
-------------------

Starting with Husk v0.5, the daemon that runs inside sandbox containers is
the **MIT-licensed** husk-daemon (this repo's `daemon/` directory). No AGPL
software ships in the runtime by default.

Earlier ``v0.x`` (x < 5) builds optionally embedded the upstream Daytona
daemon binary (AGPL-3.0). That fallback path remains supported for users
who want broader compatibility with upstream Daytona's full toolbox
surface (LSP, computer-use, recordings, etc.) — the husk-daemon currently
implements files / process subset only.

When the upstream binary is used, Husk's control plane communicates with
it only over HTTP and never links its source. Per the FSF's guidance on
aggregation (https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-faq.html#MereAggregation),
this does not make Husk's source a derivative work of the daemon.

